cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

The paper introduces a new challenge for computer and robotic vision, specifically in the area of object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The challenge is designed to be applicable to practical robotics applications, indicating a connection to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of gaussian distributions for expressing spatial uncertainty suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the evaluation of probabilistic detections using a new probability-based detection quality measure suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on practical applications and the use of video sequences suggests a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
